Heat oven to 400 degrees F. Cook and stir chicken in large skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium-high heat 4 to 5 min. or until done. Stir in 1 tablespoon barbecue sauce. Spread pizza crust with remaining barbecue sauce; top with chicken, vegetables and cheese. Place crust directly on middle oven rack. Bake 8 min. or until cheese is melted.